                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <ab type="script"/>
                        <date notBefore="1400" to="1599">15th-16th century</date>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <desc>
                           Some palaoegraphical features: 
                           ሎ has the loop marking the 7th order sometimes attached directly to the body of the letter, without the linking line; 
                           ቆ, ቶ, ዐ, የ, ደ, ጸ have angular shape; 
                           መ, ሠ and the numeral  ፱ have angular loops; 
                           the left stroke of ዘ, ሰ, and በ is slightly slanted; 
                           ቍ and ጕ are written without linking line; 
                           the numerals are sometimes written without dashes; 
                           ፪ has angular and not separated loops.
                      </desc>
                        <seg type="rubrication">
                        </seg>
                     </handNote>
